{"word":"χρονίζω","slug":"χρονίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χρονίζω</b></el> <el>(χρονίζω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:χρόνος'><el>χρόνος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to spend time</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <i>to take time, tarry, linger, delay, be slow</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to delay</i> to do, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <el>χρονίζον μένειν</el> to remain <i>long</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be prolonged</i> or <i>protracted</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to grow up</i>, <el>χρονισθείς</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}